{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7AbSdZ6BWiV4xGp7Ko","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Both tests pass.\n\n**The bug** was in `src/money.js`. The function's contract says the discount applies to the **order subtotal** and is rounded to the nearest cent **once**. Instead, the code applied the discount to each line separately and rounded each line, so the per-line rounding errors accumulated — producing the off-by-one-cent charges billing saw.\n\n**The fix:** sum the exact integer subtotal first, then apply the discount and round a single time:\n\n```js\nlet subtotal = 0;\nfor (const line of lines) {\n  subtotal += line.unitCents * line.qty;\n}\nreturn Math.round(subtotal * (1 - discountPct / 100));\n```\n\nI also added a regression test that reproduces the exact drift (two lines totaling 667 cents at 10% off → the old code returned 601/$6.01, the correct answer is 600/$6.00).\n\nOne related note I didn't change: `src/report.js` has a `// TODO: rounding here is sketchy?` comment, but its `(cents / 100).toFixed(2)` is actually correct — it's just formatting already-rounded integer cents. The real fault was upstream in `money.js`, which both `invoice.js` and `report.js` depend on."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":232,"cache_read_input_tokens":24791,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":232},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbd6aaab-8cc6-4693-a4a6-c4b2b1007fc4","uuid":"e7b5c83d-4d9f-477f-b702-092c0189a320","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:36:57.089Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7AaLejkZeVS3jdrTWt"}
